Classes in simzombie.engine used by simzombie.engine
Agent
          Basic template for the Agent class
AgentType
          A storage class that holds information about the typings of agents AgentTypes are assigned unique identifiers when created, so each simulation will have their own unique collection of AgentTypes.
Parameters
          Contains all the standard parameters that all simulations executed in SimZombie should implement This class is Abstract, as is it recommended that simulation types extend this class to include parameters which are specific to that simulation only.
Parameters.TimeOfDay
          This may be specific to zombie simulations only, but also may not.
SavedSimulation
          Class that structures a Simulation in a way that it can be saved Simulation IO uses this class, which saves an ordered list of SavedStep objects which relate to the individual steps of a simulation.
SavedStep
          Stores ALL the information about a single step of a simulation When stored successively (as in SavedSimulation) they can be used to recreate a simulation
SavedStep.StepComparator
          Orders steps in a list based on their step number, which is their position with a simulation
